Which of the following commands will obtain the date in seconds since the epoch and placeit into a variable called DATE within a shell script?
A)  DATE="$(date +%s)"
B)  DATE="date"
C)  DATE="$(date)";
D)  DATE="$date %s"
A
A. The provided answer performs command substitution and places the value from theresulting command into a variable. Note the use of +%s formatting on the date, which thenformats the output as seconds since the epoch, as specified in the question. Option C willprovide the date within the DATE variable but will not format it as specified.
